title: PPPP’s Bilawal Bhutto Zardari wins NA-196 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian Candidate Bilawal Bhutto Zardari has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-196 Shehdadkot-I by securing 85,370 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan candidate Nasir Mehmood, who bagged 34,499 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 34.89 percent.
